5. g6 {Black fianchettoes the bishop on g7 to increase its power and also directly combat the critical e5 square. This, however, comes at a price - he seriously weakens the dark squares around his king. This is where we will base our strategy.   Also, this line can transpose from something else - if Black had fianchettoed the bishop before and only now or a move later played ...d7-d5.} 
6. Bg2
