11. Qe2 {The critical position of the variation.} 
11. g5 {If White will be allowed to play Nf1 and Bf4 with h2-h4 to follow, White's kingside attack will become too strong.} 
12. Nxg5
12. Qxe5 {Black wants to trade queens - don't allow it.} 
13. Nde4
13. dxe4
14. Bf4 {The better way of playing this position!} 
14. Qf6
15. Bxe4 {We are threatening a fork on h7!} 
15. e5
16. Bxh7+ {This appears to be stronger than taking with the knight.} 
16. Kh8
17. Qh5
