1. Nf3
1. d5 {In the first chapter, we're going to examine the most popular system that Black can choose. Not surprisingly, it's also the most played system in online chess platforms against the Reti. As I already said in the Introduction, you can get here with1.e4as well, if your opponent plays either the French defense or Sicilian Paulsen with2...e6.} 
2. g3 {The King's Indian attack is a branch of the Reti opening. In case you're looking towards more improvisation later to include moves like c2-c4 or b2-b3, you can focus on it to broaden your understanding of the arising positions.} 
2. Nf6
3. Bg2
3. e6 {There's a good reason why this approach is so popular for Black - he aims for a quick short castle and is pretty flexible with the choices later. The only minor drawback - the light-squared bishop is slightly passive but often it's moved to the a8-h1 diagonal.} 
4. O-O
4. Be7
5. d3 {White's plan is pretty simple - aim for a kingside attack which will start with closing the center. Black soon will be at crossroads.} 
5. a5 {Since the development of modern chess engines, an aggressive side-pawn movement in many openings has become quite a trend, at least in the professional circuit. The idea is to early grab space advantage and gather some information, on how the opponent is going to meet it, while not yet defining his setup. Smart!} 
6. Nbd2
6. a4
7. a3 {It's a good idea to block the pawn on a4, not allowing it to advance to a3. If this would happen, the black pawn on a3 could cause White some headaches later, especially in an endgame. Normally this approach from Black should transpose to the main lines of the chapter, or at least something very similar.} 
7. c5
8. e4
8. Nc6
9. Re1 {Now the game steers towards a familiar path. Normally the line will simply transpose but there's one interesting option from Black that I'd like to show you.} 
9. h6 {It was quite a bit surprising to me when I faced this move in 2021 FIDE Grand Swiss against one of the strongest German players Matthias Bluebaum. Black has quite an odd idea prepared! Stay alert - Black has not castled yet.} 
