15. Ba6 {Either with this or another move, Black is pretending that things at the queenside matter more.} 
16. Qd2 {And now it starts to look even more real!} 
16. Kh7 {Another human move but now the king on h7 can jump under some unpleasant checks, which gives White the following idea.} 
17. c4 {With this typical move White kills Black's initiative at the queenside. Notice that Black can't take on c4 twice because of Qc2+.} 
17. bxc3
18. bxc3
18. Rb8
19. c4 {White combines the kingside attack with active operations in the center.} 
19. Nb6
20. Nfh2 {Now that the black knight is gone from defending the f6 square, the sacrificial motif on h6 is back on the table.} 
20. Qc7
21. Nxh6
21. gxh6
22. Ng4 {Black is toast.} 
