9. c3 {White prepares to play e4-e5, so that it can be strengthened with d3-d4. Black has a few choices.} 
9. Qc7 {Black guards both the e5 and d4 squares against White's advancements. What to do?} 
10. Nf1 {Unfortunately, the idea to play Bf4 to push away the black queen and then play e4-e5 does not work - Black can effectively close the center.} 
10. d4
11. Bf4
11. e5 {White's kingside piece placement makes no sense.} 
