5. Nd7
6. O-O {White gives another chance for Black to play ...e7-e5.} 
6. e6 {A careful move - now that Black has traded the light-squared bishop, it's a good idea to build a brick wall.} 
7. d3 {The most flexible idea - White wants to play next f3-f4, bring the knight to f3, followed by such moves as Be3, c2-c3 and push forward the a-pawn. It is possible to play d2-d4 immediately but then you lose some of the flexibility, including closing the bishop's diagonal on e3. Also, the pawn on d4 at some point could become a target of Black's counterplay with ...c6-c5.} 
