3. Qc7 {This continuation recently has gained some popularity among Caro-Kann specialists. Black wants to play ...e5 next.} 
4. g3 {Actually, here White is quite flexible with choices. You can play4.Nc3and see what kind of setup your opponent chooses - there's a fair chance that the position will transpose to some sort of a standard Caro-Kann as Black might just take on e4.4.Nbd2makes sense, with an idea to meet Black's4...e5with5.d4where the black queen on c7 is slightly misplaced - you might remember a mention of this idea earlier in the chapter.Even4.exd5with c2-c4 and Nc3 to follow is interesting. We'll try to stick to the King's Indian attack values.} 
