14. Bf4 {You know, what to do - attack at the kingside! The most promising plan looks c2-c3 and d3-d4, so that you have more free hands for the attack, without worrying about the safety of the e5 pawn.   The light-squared bishop can be rerouted to d3 to join the attack but when doing this, you will have to watch out for any Black's counterplay at the queenside.   Perhaps don't rush with the immediate h4-h5 as after Black's ... h7-h6 there might be a sudden counter-attack with ...g6-g5 and your e5 pawn is still quite vulnerable. As an alternative, you can consider c2-c4 to open your light-squared bishop on g2.14...h6This is how the game might continue - I will illustrate a possible scenario.(14...Nc615.h5?!Be careful to not rush with this maneuver.15...h6!Albeit this might be still good for White, it unnecessarily complicates the game).15.Qd2Kh716.c3White prepares to secure the center - I guess, it's difficult to make a progress without properly defending the e5 pawn. The difference here is that you have already forced Black to give up his light-squared bishop.16...Nc617.d4cxd418.cxd4You have just one rule - don't blunder any forks and don't trade queens.18...Na519.Qc2Nb320.Rad1Rc821.Qd3The queen on d3 stands a little better on b1 - look for the reason, if Black plays ...Qc7! White is threatening to play h4-h5.21...Kg8(21...Qc722.h5Qc223.Bf1!A very powerful move - White doesn't allow Black to play ...g6-g5 as the pin is still alive. That's the difference between the queen on d3 or b1. Black is losing something real quick).22.Bf1Here comes the bishop.22...Nb623.Qe3Kh724.Bd3Again, White's threat of h4-h5 looks devastating!24...Nc425.Qe2Kg8Black once again dodges the pin.26.Bb1b5If Black plays ...h6-h5, it will only fuel White's attack with the eventual g3-g4.27.h5g528.Qd3White has a winning attack - you have to appreciate the powerful battery of the queen and the bishop!28...Re829.Qh7+Kf830.Bxg5!There might be other moves, this is the most forcing.30...hxg531.h6Bxh632.Qxh6+Ke733.Nxg5White is winning.  I hope that you liked the course! I tried to stick to the traditional values of the kingside attack but sometimes there's nothing better than a simple positional game. You will notice that White's plans often are very similar, and that's why it makes it such an easy and practical weapon to employ. Happy hunting and I wish you to score a lot of beautiful and memorable victories!} 
