 {Here Black has already committed to ...c7-c5. He intends to continue with ...Nc6. The best plan for Black here is widely considered an aggressive queenside pawn push, starting with ...b7-b5, ...a7-a5 and pushing both pawns as far as possible in order to seek counterplay on the queenside. White should focus on the kingside.} 1. e5 {This maneuver is recommended only after Black has castled short. If you will play it while the black king is still in the center, not only Black could castle the long way and ruin your kingside attack chances, but he could also launch an unexpected kingside counter-strike with ...h7-h6 and ...g7-g5, going after your e5 pawn.   A piece of advice - if the black king is still in the center and Black plays ...b7-b5, most likely he doesn't want to castle long. If Black plays some slower moves like ...Qc7 or ...b7-b6, he's thinking about it.} 
1. Nfd7
2. Nf1 {White's plan is almost always the same - checkmate the black king. You can toy with the order of the moves. Black's counterplay at the kingside with ...f7-f6 or ...f7-f5 is rarely good but you should not forget about it. If that happens, take the pawn on f6, and don't allow Black to close down the kingside.} 
2. Nc6
3. Bf4 {Depending on the moment, don't miss Black's unexpected ...g7-g5-g4 maneuver, which might cost you the e5 pawn. Consider including h2-h4 first, taking into account Black's next move ...f7-f6. Also, in these positions, it's a stronger idea to position on f4 the bishop, not the f-pawn.} 
3. b5
4. h4
4. a5
5. N1h2 {The traditional way for the knight to reach the g4 square. An alternate route is through the e3 square – this is particularly interesting if Black has the queen on c7 – this gives White extra ideas with Nxd5 and e5-e6.} 
5. b4
6. h5 {You want to play h5-h6 and Black should stop it.} 
6. h6
7. Ng4 {The most traditional plan - White is threatening with sacrificing something on h6 to expose the black king. An alternative idea is to push forward the g-pawn but this requires some preparation with Kh1, Rg1, and Bh3. Black might meet the kingside assault with a proper counter-strike in the center with ...f7-f6, so make sure you don't miss it.} 
