7. g6 {I already mentioned that while I was writing the course, I was practicing a lot of additional King's Indian attack games, with both colors. In January of 2023, I happened to play this variation against Chess. com's latest sensation, the innocent-looking cat Mittens (a chess bot), who played in the same manner, as I was playing against the French GM Chabanon 7 years ago! The idea to fianchetto the bishop on g7 came from my own game against a strong Russian theoretician GM Ildar Khairullin when I was playing with White.} 
8. Be3 {Actually, I would start with f3-f4.} 
8. Bg7 {In the game against Khairullin, Black had developed the kingside knight to e7 instead which perhaps is a little more flexible but hardly changes the character of the game.} 
9. c3
9. O-O
10. f4
10. e6
11. Qb3
11. Qc7
12. a4 {A tricky question - should Black respond with ...a7-a5?} 
12. Rfd8 {I decided not to.12...a5In the near future for Black it could be difficult to seek counterplay with ...c6-c5 as that would give up the b5 square. How important is it, it's tough to say.} 
13. Nd2
13. Bf8
14. a5 {Another question - should Black allow White to push a5-a6? The far-advanced pawn in an endgame could prove to be a problem.} 
14. a6 {Not the best choice as it creates a permanent weakness on b7.14...Ne815.a6?!b5The white pawn on a6 itself actually can become a weakness. However, the thing is - White doesn't have to rush with the pawn push and the threat will be hanging in the air. An unpleasant situation for Black to be in, unless he wants to evaluate the threat after every single move.} 
15. Nf3
15. Bc5
16. d4
16. Bf8
17. Ne5 {White has a significant space advantage but Black remains solid.} 
17. Ne8
18. Qc2
18. Nd6 {Almost the decisive mistake! Black should push ...c6-c5 to make sure that White doesn't close the queenside for good to focus on the kingside attack.18...c519.c4!This is what I was afraid of - that White's bishop on g2 will become powerful. However, Black already didn't have any choice.19...cxd420.Bxd4Nxe521.fxe5!Limiting the black knight's options.21...Bc522.Bxc5Qxc523.Rfc1White is pushing but with a perfect defense Black should be able to hold this.} 
19. Rfe1 {Mittens didn't realize the opportunity just yet.19.b4!White could have sealed the queenside immediately.} 
19. Nb5
20. Bf1
20. Nd6 {Another wasted chance to push ...c6-c5.} 
21. Bd3
21. Nf5
22. b4 {Finally Mittens picked up the idea and that's it - Black is doomed. Watch the engine to build up a powerful attack at the kingside.} 
22. Nf6
23. g4
